title: Google\Cloud\Security\PublicCA\V1beta1\CreateExternalAccountKeyRequest
name: CreateExternalAccountKeyRequest
description:
Creates a new [ExternalAccountKey][google.cloud.security.publicca.v1beta1.ExternalAccountKey] in a given project.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.security.publicca.v1beta1.CreateExternalAccountKeyRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The parent resource where this external_account_key will be created. Format: projects/[project_id]/locations/[location]. At present only the "global" location is supported.

params.name: data.external_account_key
params.description: Required. The external account key to create. This field only exists to future-proof the API. At present, all fields in ExternalAccountKey are output only and all values are ignored. For the purpose of the CreateExternalAccountKeyRequest, set it to a default/empty value.
